WEBVTT

00:01.900 --> 00:02.769
<i>
So here's what you missed
on Glee. Will's dating</i>

00:02.836 --> 00:04.705
<i>The hot substitute, holly
holliday. She's totally sassy</i>

00:04.772 --> 00:06.773
<i>And you can really see
why he's into her.
Sexy.</i>

00:06.841 --> 00:08.508
<i>Quinn and Finn are back
together in a big way, and so</i>

00:08.576 --> 00:10.943
<i>Is the Glee club. They did
original songs, and now they're</i>

00:11.012 --> 00:12.713
<i>Headed to new york.
Get out! Go!</i>

00:12.780 --> 00:14.381
<i>But sue thinks will made her
lose at nationals, and she's</i>

00:14.449 --> 00:16.216
<i>Sort of gone over the edge,
even for her, and that's saying</i>

00:16.283 --> 00:18.318
<i>Something, and that's what you
missed on Glee!</i>

00:21.522 --> 00:23.357
(bell ringing)

00:26.227 --> 00:28.729
All right. We need $5,000

00:28.796 --> 00:30.230
To pay for our trip
to nationals in new york.

00:30.298 --> 00:32.399
What happened to the money
that we got from the cheerios!?

00:32.467 --> 00:35.068
I guess sue was hiding it
in offshore accounts

00:35.136 --> 00:36.803
In the cayman islands,
and we're having some trouble

00:36.871 --> 00:38.305
Accessing some of it.

00:38.373 --> 00:39.740
Any of it.

00:42.010 --> 00:44.811
This is salt water taffy.

00:44.879 --> 00:46.313
Ah, I love salt water.

00:46.381 --> 00:48.448
When I was a student here,
we paid for our entire trip

00:48.516 --> 00:50.650
To nationals, selling this.

00:50.718 --> 00:51.852
Classroom to classroom,

00:51.919 --> 00:52.953
Door to door,

00:53.021 --> 00:55.989
We pushed this stuff like crack.

00:56.057 --> 00:57.391
And so will we.

00:57.458 --> 01:00.560
So, to make $5,000

01:00.628 --> 01:02.362
At 25 cents apiece,

01:02.430 --> 01:05.632
We need to sell 20,000
pieces of taffy.

01:05.700 --> 01:07.901
Wait, do you honestly think that
we can sell 20,000 anythings?

01:07.969 --> 01:09.770
I mean, we won regionals

01:09.837 --> 01:12.139
For the first time since
dinosaurs roamed the planet,

01:12.206 --> 01:14.841
And I still got a freaking
cherry icee facial.

01:14.909 --> 01:18.779
Oh, my god.
I'm so sorry.

01:18.846 --> 01:19.913
Yeah.
Santana is right.

01:19.981 --> 01:22.349
Nobody cares about us.

01:22.417 --> 01:23.717
I can't listen to this.

01:23.785 --> 01:24.885
Mike, are you okay?

01:24.952 --> 01:26.420
No.

01:26.487 --> 01:29.356
You guys complain all the time
about being mistreated,

01:29.424 --> 01:32.059
But you have no idea what it's
like to work your butt off

01:32.126 --> 01:34.795
For something and have everyone,
even your friends, ignore you.

01:34.862 --> 01:36.797
I am so trying to remember
his name right now.

01:36.864 --> 01:39.299
Artie, tina, brittany and
I are on the brainiacs.

01:39.367 --> 01:40.767
Isn't that the academic
decathlon team?

01:40.835 --> 01:41.902
Wait. We have one of those?

01:41.969 --> 01:43.303
Yes, we do.

01:43.371 --> 01:45.105
<i>And the four of us went
on the smartypants show,</i>

01:45.173 --> 01:47.641
And beat carmel high to go to
the academic decathlon finals

01:47.708 --> 01:50.277
In detroit next week.
What? You guys were on tv?

01:50.344 --> 01:52.179
Well, why didn't you
tell us about it?

01:52.246 --> 01:53.713
All:
We did!

01:53.781 --> 01:56.283
Wait, I... I get the three of
you being on the team...

01:56.350 --> 01:58.952
Is it because two of them are
asian, and artie wears glasses?

01:59.020 --> 02:02.155
No... But brittany?

02:02.223 --> 02:05.058
Liz schneider was our fourth,
but she got rubella.

02:05.126 --> 02:07.694
Her parents are hippies who
don't believe in vaccinations.

02:07.762 --> 02:10.062
Brittany was the only person
we could find on short notice.

02:10.131 --> 02:12.499
<i>Artie:
We bribed her with dots.</i>

02:12.567 --> 02:14.234
<i>That sunshine corazon</i>

02:14.302 --> 02:16.069
<i>That rachel sent to a crack
house was on the other team.</i>

02:16.137 --> 02:17.437
I'll take "deadly cyclones,"
please.

02:17.505 --> 02:18.939
Right on, soul sister.

02:19.006 --> 02:20.474
In 1970...

02:20.541 --> 02:23.043
The bhola cyclone.

02:23.111 --> 02:24.845
Correct again.

02:24.912 --> 02:27.414
<i>Artie: Luckily, we had
our own secret weapon.</i>

02:29.117 --> 02:30.550
I'll take "cat diseases."

02:30.618 --> 02:32.085
I won't!

02:32.153 --> 02:33.720
(audience laughing)
the first known case

02:33.788 --> 02:37.491
Of this disease was first
diagnosed in calcutta in 2001.

02:37.558 --> 02:39.860
Feline aids?

02:39.927 --> 02:41.595
(bell chiming)

02:41.662 --> 02:43.163
Rod:
Correct. Bonus question.

02:43.231 --> 02:44.731
Ringworm.

02:44.799 --> 02:46.133
Conjunctivitis.

02:46.200 --> 02:48.101
Kidney failure.

02:48.169 --> 02:49.436
(applause)

02:49.504 --> 02:52.639
Now, on to our final
speed round question.

02:52.707 --> 02:55.208
Whoever buzzes in first
and answers correctly

02:55.276 --> 02:58.545
Will win the title and go on to
our finals next week in detroit.

02:58.613 --> 03:02.549
Our final category,
"white rappers."

03:02.617 --> 03:05.185
Sadly, we can't afford to go to
the finals, so we're gonna have

03:05.253 --> 03:07.120
To forfeit.
Why don't you just have
your parents pay for it?

03:07.188 --> 03:09.055
Because we shouldn't have to.
We're a school club.

03:09.123 --> 03:10.157
The school should
pay for it.

03:10.224 --> 03:11.491
It's a matter of pride.

03:11.559 --> 03:13.226
You guys are absolutely right.

03:13.294 --> 03:14.928
How much do you need
to make the trip?

03:14.996 --> 03:16.363
With gas and motels,

03:16.430 --> 03:20.033
If we only eat funyuns,
uh, $250.

03:20.101 --> 03:21.401
Which means...

03:23.971 --> 03:27.240
We just need
to sell more taffy.

03:31.412 --> 03:34.781
I'm sure you're wondering why
I called you all together here

03:34.849 --> 03:36.583
In the dead of night,

03:36.651 --> 03:39.386
When I'm normally out
bow-hunting for hobos.

03:39.453 --> 03:41.288
Dustin goolsby,
coach of vocal adrenaline.

03:41.355 --> 03:42.689
Sandy ryerson,

03:42.757 --> 03:44.925
Defrocked educator
and legendary friend of dorothy.

03:44.992 --> 03:46.493
Terri schuester, shrew.

03:46.561 --> 03:47.994
I'm also an assistant manager.

03:48.062 --> 03:51.631
We all have one
very important thing in common.

03:51.699 --> 03:54.000
We all hate will schuester.

03:54.068 --> 03:55.001
I have a question.

03:55.069 --> 03:58.471
Are you single?
Uh, I'm not gay.

03:58.539 --> 04:02.609
I don't care. You're hunky,
and I'm what they call
"predatory gay."

04:02.677 --> 04:04.644
I'll admit I've been on
a bit of a losing streak,

04:04.712 --> 04:08.415
Having lost regionals, and if
will schuster wins at nationals,

04:08.482 --> 04:10.016
My role as reigning champion

04:10.084 --> 04:12.719
At this school will be usurped.

04:12.787 --> 04:14.254
I'm asking you for your help.

04:14.322 --> 04:16.790
Our mission?
To destroy the Glee club.

04:16.857 --> 04:20.093
We'll target their fragile sense
of self-esteem

04:20.161 --> 04:23.730
So that they implode long before
they can make it to nationals.

04:23.798 --> 04:24.864
And I call this union...

04:26.033 --> 04:27.767
...The league of doom.

04:27.835 --> 04:29.236
Ooh.

04:29.303 --> 04:30.837
Okay, first of all,
that is a ridiculous name.

04:30.905 --> 04:32.138
And second of all,
what kind of a meeting

04:32.206 --> 04:33.540
Doesn't have bagels
or something?

04:33.608 --> 04:35.408
Wow, it would be hard
to be married to you.

04:35.476 --> 04:36.876
And for the record?
Or mixed nuts...

04:36.944 --> 04:38.545
I am trying to move
on with my life.

04:38.613 --> 04:39.980
I don't hate will schuester.

04:40.047 --> 04:41.281
But you do hate the Glee club.

04:41.349 --> 04:43.016
That's true. I do.

04:43.084 --> 04:44.684
And I am looking
for a new hobby.

04:44.752 --> 04:46.019
Henceforth, you will be known

04:46.087 --> 04:47.621
By the following
super villain nicknames.

04:47.688 --> 04:49.723
Sandy ryerson,
you are the pink dagger.

04:49.790 --> 04:51.691
Yes!
You are the honey badger,

04:51.759 --> 04:53.159
Nature's most ferocious animal.

04:53.227 --> 04:54.461
Look it up on youtube.

04:54.528 --> 04:56.730
Dustin goolsby?
Sergeant handsome.

04:56.797 --> 04:59.532
My codename

04:59.600 --> 05:01.034
Will be general Zod.
Hold up.

05:01.102 --> 05:03.036
I coach the winningest
Glee club in history.

05:03.104 --> 05:05.005
We're a lock to beat mckinley
at nationals as it is.

05:05.072 --> 05:06.539
Why would I want
to get involved in this?

05:06.607 --> 05:08.642
Well, because, sergeant, you
strike me as a bit of a tool

05:08.709 --> 05:11.411
Who enjoys playing mind games
with your opponents.

05:11.479 --> 05:12.512
That's true.
I really do like doing that.

05:12.580 --> 05:13.647
Legion of evil?

05:13.714 --> 05:15.949
League of doom.
You can count me in.

05:16.017 --> 05:18.385
Although I am enjoying
my second career

05:18.452 --> 05:20.420
As a small-time
medical marijuana dealer.

05:20.488 --> 05:22.222
Okey-dokey.
It doesn't change the fact

05:22.290 --> 05:23.957
That william took my job.

05:24.025 --> 05:25.158
Here are your beepers.

05:25.226 --> 05:27.327
You will await
further instructions.

05:27.395 --> 05:31.197
And until then,
we will be known only as...

05:31.265 --> 05:33.500
The legion of evil.
I don't think I was listening
when you said what our name was.

05:33.567 --> 05:34.668
Wait a second. Is it
"league" or "legion"?

05:34.735 --> 05:36.169
Worst henchmen ever.

05:39.940 --> 05:42.809
I missed you so
much last week.

05:42.877 --> 05:44.811
So what do you want
to do tomorrow night?

05:44.879 --> 05:47.047
Whoa, there, cowboy, we haven't
even had our pizza yet.

05:47.114 --> 05:48.782
I'm just trying
to get you when I can.

05:51.085 --> 05:52.285
(laughs)

05:52.353 --> 05:54.487
You know, this is actually

05:54.555 --> 05:57.457
The first relationship
I've had where the girl

05:57.525 --> 05:59.626
Hasn't been all over me
to spend more time with her.

05:59.694 --> 06:00.894
Well, get used to it.

06:00.961 --> 06:02.228
I'm a sub.

06:02.296 --> 06:03.596
I'm a rolling stone.

06:03.664 --> 06:06.032
I warned you that being in
a relationship with me meant

06:06.100 --> 06:07.567
Being in a constant
state of wanting.

06:07.635 --> 06:11.204
I am both awesome and
unavailable at the same time.

06:11.272 --> 06:13.540
You're kind of awesome.
(laughs)

06:13.607 --> 06:15.108
What do you think about
my taffy sale plan

06:15.176 --> 06:16.509
To send the brainiacs
to detroit?

06:16.577 --> 06:20.146
Um, I think it's
as terrible as the word

06:20.214 --> 06:21.548
"brainiacs," but...

06:21.615 --> 06:23.850
Oh, okay. Here's
your problem, all right?

06:23.918 --> 06:26.052
You're thinking
too small, okay?

06:26.120 --> 06:28.988
That crazy ex-wife of yours
messed with your brain

06:29.056 --> 06:31.124
And now you think
you can't dream.

06:31.192 --> 06:32.525
Okay. Well,
what's your idea?

06:32.593 --> 06:35.595
A night of neglect.

06:35.663 --> 06:37.997
That actually sounds
like life with my ex-wife.

06:38.065 --> 06:41.101
Hilarious. No, seriously,
here's what you need to do.

06:41.168 --> 06:42.836
Have a benefit.

06:42.903 --> 06:46.005
You know how they do on tv when
there's, like, an earthquake,

06:46.073 --> 06:49.843
Or they want to raise money
for, like, a sad disease.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.077
That's actually
a really good idea.

06:51.145 --> 06:52.779
I know it is.

06:52.847 --> 06:54.781
See, your kids are feeling
really neglected, right?

06:54.849 --> 06:56.716
So you fill the auditorium
with people who are there

06:56.784 --> 06:58.218
To hear them sing, and poof!

06:58.285 --> 07:00.653
Oh, I'm loving this.

07:00.721 --> 07:02.756
And we can sell tickets.

07:02.823 --> 07:05.892
And it is a perfect place
to practice for nationals.

07:05.960 --> 07:07.360
And you know the best part?

07:07.428 --> 07:09.796
We're only going to do songs
by neglected artists.

07:11.499 --> 07:13.733
Because it's
"a night of neglect."

07:13.801 --> 07:16.269
Can you define what you mean
by "neglected artist"?

07:16.337 --> 07:19.406
Um, someone whose brilliance
isn't always appreciated.

07:19.473 --> 07:20.473
Oh, so you mean like me.

07:20.541 --> 07:22.542
I mean, like all of us.

07:22.610 --> 07:24.544
All right, everyone,
next Saturday night,

07:24.612 --> 07:25.779
In our auditorium,

07:25.846 --> 07:27.981
Mckinley high's first annual

07:28.048 --> 07:30.850
"night of neglect" fund-raiser
benefit is officially a go!

07:30.918 --> 07:32.085
(applause)

07:33.858 --> 07:35.292
(bell ringing)

07:35.359 --> 07:36.993
Sergeant handsome,
walk with me.

07:37.061 --> 07:39.329
I'm surprised
you even saw me.

07:39.397 --> 07:41.131
I was blending in
pretty well back there.

07:41.198 --> 07:43.133
Here's your mission. Word on
the street is that schuester

07:43.200 --> 07:45.669
And that substitute
holly holliday are official.

07:45.736 --> 07:47.037
I need you to
break them up.

07:47.104 --> 07:49.406
She's looser than a
thrift store turtleneck

07:49.473 --> 07:51.274
And probably
just as diseased.

07:51.342 --> 07:52.609
Just my type.

07:52.677 --> 07:54.577
Psst! Ready for my
close-up, general zog.

07:54.645 --> 07:56.179
Sandy, how do you manage
to enter a building

07:56.247 --> 07:58.214
Without setting off
all the fire alarms?

07:58.282 --> 08:00.317
You know, I have to say, with
all this sneaking around,

08:00.384 --> 08:01.918
I have never
felt more alive.

08:01.986 --> 08:03.520
What's my assignment?

08:03.587 --> 08:04.821
Pink dagger, I just learned

08:04.889 --> 08:06.623
That the Glee club
is performing a benefit concert.

08:06.691 --> 08:08.258
It's just
the opening we need.

08:08.326 --> 08:10.260
There's a student club
I want you to sponsor.

08:10.328 --> 08:12.128
Heckling.

08:12.196 --> 08:14.064
The world's
second oldest profession.

08:14.131 --> 08:15.165
Hell am I doing in here?

08:15.232 --> 08:16.232
Good. Louder.

08:16.300 --> 08:17.834
In olden times,

08:17.902 --> 08:19.269
Hecklers provided
a needed service

08:19.337 --> 08:21.771
To the medieval community.
Pink dagger, if I may.

08:21.839 --> 08:24.741
Welcome to the very first
meeting of the heckling club.

08:24.809 --> 08:26.176
You set me up.
You told me

08:26.243 --> 08:27.711
I was supposed to come here
to get homework help.

08:27.778 --> 08:29.646
Congratulations. You're all in.

08:30.815 --> 08:33.982
I'm really confused.

08:34.051 --> 08:35.684
(bell ringing)
I'm totally doing lykke li.

08:35.753 --> 08:37.654
She's bjork meets
florence and the machine,

08:37.722 --> 08:39.054
And a promising new talent.

08:39.123 --> 08:40.390
What about you, mike?

08:40.457 --> 08:42.859
The mike chang dance dance
revolution.

08:42.927 --> 08:44.728
I'm tired of my dancing
being overshadowed

08:44.795 --> 08:46.029
By all of you
guys' singing.

08:46.097 --> 08:48.798
It's going to be just me
and my sweet moves

08:48.866 --> 08:50.233
On that stage.

08:50.301 --> 08:52.736
You're forgetting about
the most neglected artist

08:52.803 --> 08:53.970
This Glee club's
ever seen--

08:54.038 --> 08:55.238
Aretha franklin.

08:55.306 --> 08:57.407
Neglected?
She's, like, the queen of soul.

08:57.475 --> 08:59.676
See, I auditioned for this club

08:59.744 --> 09:02.245
Singing "respect,"
and she's gotten none since.

09:02.313 --> 09:03.413
So I'm doing aretha.

09:03.481 --> 09:04.414
Awesome, mercedes.

09:04.482 --> 09:05.849
Awesome, all of you guys.

09:05.916 --> 09:08.017
Those songs are great appetizers
to my main course.

09:08.085 --> 09:10.320
Celine dion's "my
heart will go on."

09:10.388 --> 09:11.454
It's gonna be our finale.

09:11.522 --> 09:12.789
(imitates tires screeching)

09:12.857 --> 09:14.624
That's like the biggest
song of all time.

09:14.692 --> 09:15.959
No. You don't understand.

09:16.026 --> 09:18.228
Celine isn't the
neglected artist, I am.

09:18.295 --> 09:20.630
I was kind of hoping
to do the closing number.

09:20.698 --> 09:23.199
Hey, you guys remember
sunshine corazon?

09:23.267 --> 09:24.634
You are a terrible spy.

09:24.702 --> 09:26.202
Seriously, with your size,

09:26.270 --> 09:27.871
You easily could have stayed
in the air ducts for days.

09:27.938 --> 09:29.339
I'm not a spy.

09:29.407 --> 09:31.274
I heard about your benefit
concert on facebook,

09:31.342 --> 09:32.809
And I wanted to perform.

09:32.877 --> 09:35.612
I know what it feels like
to be in academic decathlon.

09:35.679 --> 09:38.314
No one pays attention to you.
No one cares.

09:38.382 --> 09:39.983
It's not right.
We study so hard.

09:40.050 --> 09:41.317
Yeah, but you're
in vocal adrenaline.

09:41.385 --> 09:42.552
How do we know
we can trust you?

09:42.620 --> 09:45.021
Because I have nothing
against any of you.

09:45.089 --> 09:48.525
I have 600 twitter followers.
I can get all of them to come.

09:48.592 --> 09:49.959
How many tickets
have we sold so far?

09:50.027 --> 09:52.228
Four. No one's interested.
It's just sad.

09:52.296 --> 09:54.998
Please, just let me
show you what I can do.

09:55.065 --> 09:57.300
I would like to sing
the perfect song about neglect,

09:57.368 --> 09:58.635
"all by myself."

09:58.702 --> 10:00.570
I'm such a better singer
than everyone else,

10:00.638 --> 10:02.205
So I know how it feels.

10:02.273 --> 10:04.507
I'm all alone at the top.

10:04.575 --> 10:07.610
Also, I'm really short. So even
when I'm in a group of people,

10:07.678 --> 10:09.712
It feels like I'm wandering
alone through a forest.

10:09.780 --> 10:12.115
There's no way that she's
singing in our auditorium, okay?

10:12.183 --> 10:13.650
She's the enemy.

10:13.717 --> 10:16.886
I say we give her a chance. I
mean, you owe her, rachel.

10:16.954 --> 10:19.456
You sent her to a
frickin' crack house.

10:19.523 --> 10:21.591
(slow ballad plays)

10:24.261 --> 10:27.831
♪ when I was young ♪

10:27.898 --> 10:32.535
♪ I never needed anyone ♪

10:34.505 --> 10:37.907
♪ and making love
was just for fun ♪

10:39.877 --> 10:43.213
♪ those days are gone ♪

10:45.850 --> 10:49.719
♪ living alone ♪

10:49.787 --> 10:54.090
♪ I think
of all the friends I've known ♪

10:56.660 --> 11:00.563
♪ when I dial the telephone ♪

11:02.066 --> 11:05.969
♪ nobody's home ♪

11:13.544 --> 11:19.082
♪ all by myself ♪

11:19.149 --> 11:21.184
♪ don't wanna be ♪

11:21.252 --> 11:26.256
♪ all by myself ♪

11:26.323 --> 11:29.158
♪ anymore ♪

11:29.226 --> 11:35.164
♪ all by myself ♪

11:35.232 --> 11:37.166
♪ don't wanna live ♪

11:37.234 --> 11:41.905
♪ all by myself ♪

11:41.972 --> 11:49.345
♪ anymore... ♪

11:49.413 --> 11:53.917
(applause, cheering, whooping)

11:53.984 --> 11:55.852
Go on, now!

11:59.456 --> 12:07.363
♪ don't wanna live by myself,
by myself anymore ♪

12:10.267 --> 12:14.203
♪ by myself ♪

12:14.271 --> 12:16.673
♪ anymore ♪

12:16.740 --> 12:25.815
♪ whoa, oh-oh, oh-oh. ♪

12:25.883 --> 12:28.851
(applause and cheering)
come on!

12:30.821 --> 12:33.823
So, can I perform with you guys?

12:33.891 --> 12:35.191
Absolutely not.
She's just trying

12:35.259 --> 12:37.493
To get on our good sides
so she can spy on us.

12:37.561 --> 12:38.895
You're one to talk. We told you

12:38.963 --> 12:41.397
The same thing
about jesse st. James last year.

12:41.465 --> 12:42.899
And you were right!
Finn:
This whole thing

12:42.967 --> 12:44.867
Isn't about us. It's about
helping the brainiacs.

12:44.935 --> 12:46.235
Puck:
Yeah, we need sunshine's

12:46.303 --> 12:47.770
Twitter followers to
come and pay for tickets,

12:47.838 --> 12:49.572
Or there's no point in
having a benefit at all.

12:49.640 --> 12:50.707
(sighs)

12:52.209 --> 12:55.111
Fine. Mercedes,
you're okay with being bumped

12:55.179 --> 12:56.779
To the decidedly less glamorous
middle spot.

12:56.847 --> 12:57.981
Right?

12:58.048 --> 13:00.883
Um... Sure, I guess.

13:03.053 --> 13:05.321
Absolutely.

13:10.094 --> 13:11.794
(school bell ringing)

13:11.862 --> 13:13.763
Hey, mercedes, can
I have your shoes?

13:13.831 --> 13:17.433
I promise to give you a dirty
pair of my flip-flops in return.

13:17.501 --> 13:19.135
Do you know how hard it is

13:19.203 --> 13:20.837
To find high-top, yellow
patent leather sneakers?

13:20.904 --> 13:22.372
Really? I'm surprised

13:22.439 --> 13:24.474
You didn't just give them
to me, considering

13:24.541 --> 13:25.775
How little you
think of yourself.

13:25.843 --> 13:27.910
You're the most talented singer
in Glee club,

13:27.978 --> 13:30.113
Yet you're constantly taking
the backseat to everyone.

13:30.180 --> 13:32.115
Well, what am I supposed to do?

13:32.182 --> 13:34.450
I'm-I'm tired of fighting
with rachel all the time.

13:34.518 --> 13:37.520
Okay, you're always singing
about r-e-s-p-e-c-t,

13:37.588 --> 13:39.522
But respect isn't something
you can ask for.

13:39.590 --> 13:40.857
You have to demand it.

13:40.924 --> 13:42.458
And you deserve it.

13:42.526 --> 13:44.527
You don't seem to have trouble
in that department.
Right.

13:44.595 --> 13:46.062
You know what?

13:46.130 --> 13:48.698
Neither does aretha
or j-lo or mariah.

13:48.766 --> 13:51.200
You know why? Because
they get proof every day.

13:51.268 --> 13:53.736
I heard mariah
makes appointments at 9:00 a.M.,

13:53.804 --> 13:55.938
And shows up at 4:00
in the afternoon

13:56.006 --> 13:58.775
Because she knows
people will wait.

13:58.842 --> 14:01.077
But those kinds
of demands are ridiculous.

14:01.145 --> 14:02.912
Exactly. But once
you see that no matter

14:02.980 --> 14:04.781
How ridiculous your demands,
people will meet them,

14:04.848 --> 14:06.249
You know
you have it.
Have what?

14:06.316 --> 14:09.786
Respect. And as your manager,

14:09.853 --> 14:11.120
I'd say you're
thinking too small.

14:11.188 --> 14:13.156
Wait a minute.
Since when are you my manager?

14:13.223 --> 14:15.191
Since you agreed to
give me ten percent

14:15.259 --> 14:17.927
Of whatever we can come
up with to ask for.

14:20.030 --> 14:22.131
Sister, you got yourself a deal.

14:23.988 --> 14:25.822
(whirring)

14:29.660 --> 14:31.628
Are you okay?

14:31.696 --> 14:34.297
Yup. I will be as soon
as this counter's really clean.

14:36.134 --> 14:38.835
I hear that ocd symptoms
tend to get worse

14:38.903 --> 14:40.737
When the person
is under great stress.

14:42.940 --> 14:44.441
(sniffles)

14:44.509 --> 14:46.009
Carl's gone.

14:50.548 --> 14:52.616
He asked for an annulment,

14:52.683 --> 14:55.819
Which I guess

14:55.887 --> 14:57.387
He's legally entitled to,

14:57.455 --> 15:00.190
Considering we never actually
consummated the marriage.

15:00.258 --> 15:01.158
You guys never...?

15:05.229 --> 15:06.730
At what age are you allowed

15:06.798 --> 15:09.733
To look back on your life
with nothing but regret?

15:09.801 --> 15:11.201
Is 32 too young?

15:17.542 --> 15:18.909
I actually believed

15:18.976 --> 15:21.344
That I'd have a handle
on my ocd by now.

15:23.681 --> 15:27.217
It's just been so long, and...

15:27.285 --> 15:29.119
I'm so tired.

15:34.525 --> 15:36.526
This your lunch?

15:36.594 --> 15:38.695
Yeah.

15:45.503 --> 15:47.370
What are you doing?

15:50.374 --> 15:53.443
One day, you're going to find
a way to beat this thing.

15:53.511 --> 15:55.011
Until then,

15:55.079 --> 15:57.581
I'm here for you.

15:57.648 --> 15:59.015
No judgment.

15:59.083 --> 16:01.118
Just...

16:01.185 --> 16:02.986
A friend that you can count on.

16:05.523 --> 16:07.657
Cheers.

16:13.865 --> 16:15.332
(school bell ringing)
Finn:
So, uh, the braniacs

16:15.399 --> 16:18.235
Asked us to be benefit heads
for the night of neglect.

16:18.302 --> 16:19.669
Quinn:
And we would like to select you

16:19.737 --> 16:21.004
Head of talent relations.

16:21.072 --> 16:22.305
We figured
you're probably used to relating

16:22.373 --> 16:24.274
To talent
because you're so talented.

16:24.342 --> 16:27.010
Well, first, I'm honored
that you came to me,

16:27.078 --> 16:29.546
But I think it's a little
insensitive of you to be

16:29.614 --> 16:31.615
Flaunting your
dating in my face.
Fantastic.

16:31.682 --> 16:34.618
'cause we are having problems
with one of our performers.

16:34.685 --> 16:36.786
A) I need a bowl of green m&Ms.

16:36.854 --> 16:39.389
And by bowl, I mean large bowl.
Well, really a small barrel.

16:39.457 --> 16:40.590
O... Kay.

16:40.658 --> 16:41.992
Two) I need humidifiers.

16:42.059 --> 16:45.028
Lots of humidifiers.
A team of humidifiers

16:45.096 --> 16:46.630
Whose only job is to make

16:46.697 --> 16:48.331
The air that mercedes
breathes more humid.

16:48.399 --> 16:50.667
We'll try our best.
Shh. I'm not finished.

16:50.735 --> 16:53.336
Before every performance,
I like to wash my hands.

16:53.404 --> 16:56.940
And after doing so, I like to
dry them on a fresh puppy.

16:57.008 --> 16:59.109
Excuse me?
I believe you heard Ms. Jones.

16:59.177 --> 17:01.111
In fact, if I were you, I'd
probably get a whole litter

17:01.179 --> 17:03.180
Of fluffy puppies, just in case
she decides

17:03.247 --> 17:05.382
To take a post-show shower.

17:05.449 --> 17:06.516
Stars make demands
the way that babies

17:06.584 --> 17:07.751
Make messes in their diapers.

17:07.818 --> 17:09.452
They can't help it.
What a star wants is

17:09.520 --> 17:11.154
To just feel appreciated
and respected.

17:11.222 --> 17:13.323
They just want to feel
like they're being heard.

17:13.391 --> 17:15.058
She seemed pretty serious
about the puppy.

17:15.126 --> 17:17.928
Well, obviously, hers is a
talent that we have neglected.

17:17.994 --> 17:19.229
I can relate.

17:19.297 --> 17:21.665
So leave it to me.
I'll take care of it.

17:24.234 --> 17:25.569
(british accent):
Hello, class.

17:25.636 --> 17:27.637
I am the world's most famous
and stylish divorcee

17:27.704 --> 17:30.006
Wallace simpson.

17:30.074 --> 17:32.809
I was married a bunch of times,
and then I fell in love

17:32.877 --> 17:35.245
With edward viii and made him
abdicate the throne.

17:35.313 --> 17:39.749
I had giant hands,
so a lot of people thought

17:39.817 --> 17:42.552
I was a hermaphrodite, but
that wasn't true. Others said

17:42.620 --> 17:44.287
I was a nazi sympathizer.

17:44.355 --> 17:45.822
<i>That was true.</i>

17:45.890 --> 17:48.391
Boy, did I think
that hitler showed promise!

17:48.459 --> 17:49.993
(bell rings)
(normal voice):
Tomorrow we're gonna do

17:50.061 --> 17:53.663
Catherine the great and her pet
stallion fred, so come early.

17:57.235 --> 17:59.202
